<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="904" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d904">
                    <head>Students of the Concordia Society</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 3, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p>The students of the Concordia Society, 19 members, have this day resolved to
                        unite in the address of sympathy and condolence to the American Union. In
                        the name of the Concordia:</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>A. SCHEURER, <hi rend="italic">President, Law
                                    Student</hi>.</item>
                                <item>BERGER, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>